the former conrail workers told the senate commerce committee on thursday of co-workers who consumed as much as a case of beer a day, brought bottles of liquor to work, or used marijuana, cocaine, amphetamines and other drugs
overall, drinking was encouraged on the job, especially when i was hired on,'' said ricky l. gates, who was the engineer of the three connected conrail locomotives that on jan. 4, 1987, collided with a crowded amtrak passenger train
