soybean futures prices retreated and grain futures were mostly lower in early, choppy trading today at the chicago board of trade
follow-through selling from thursday pressured the markets, while a flurry of buying by big professional traders helped offset losses, analysts said
continued heavy rains in brazil, which have eased dry, crop-threatening conditions, and other outside factors added a negative tone to the market, said victor lespinasse, an analyst with dean witter reynolds inc
it's mostly a technical trade, no big surprises,'' lespinasse said
