brussels stock exchange officials suspended trading in societe generale de belgique sa for a second straight day friday, as soaring demand for the stock highlighted the intense battle for control over belgium's biggest holding company
societe generale shares opened with offers hitting a record 8,060 francs, or $230.30 per share, up 15 percent over thursday
on thursday, italian investor carlo de benedetti had doubled his original offer to 8,000 francs, or $228.60
de benedetti claims to control 45 percent of societe generale stock. he wants 7 more percent to counter an alliance of french, belgian, luxembourg and swiss investors, which claims it controls 52 percent of societe generale shares
de benedetti disputes that claim
societe generale management, which supports the alliance, denied reports of a rift within the group on friday
there are accords between different partners to be sure this majority exists,'' said etienne davignon, a societe generale director
the italian financier has said he wanted to expand societe generale's holdings throughout europe by 1992, when the european economic community expects to have removed all internal bariers to trade among the 12 eec nations
the alliance opposing de benedetti wants the 166-year-old company to remain anchored in belgium
trading in societe generale was first halted thursday, after the share price rose to a record 7,010 francs, or $200, shortly after the stock exchange opened
the stock closed at 6,100 francs, or $174.29, wednesday and at 5,350 francs, or $152.86, tuesday. it stood at 2,155 francs, or $61.58, last october, when hints of the looming takeover battle began to appear
on friday, a new freeze forced any trading in the share off the exchange to the unofficial market
this market has accounted for millions of transactions on given days over the course of the last few months, but has largely dried up in recent days to the lack of available shares
we had offers as high as 10,000 francs (or $285) per share but had no paper for them,'' said one dealer at a major brokerage firm
the alliance battling de benedetti is formed around the french firms compagnie financiere de suez, an investment firm, compagnie generale d'electricite, an industrial company, and societe financiere et industrielle gaz et eaux
together they control 36 percent while an international group around belgium's biggest insurance company, groupe ag, controls another 16 percent
the 166-year-old societe generale has interests in some 1,400 firms world-wide and in about half of belgium's top 50 companies
metromedia co. has signed a definitive agreement to acquire the ponderosa inc. restaurant chain for an undisclosed amount, the company announced friday
metromedia, a privately-held telecommunications and technology holding company, said it planned to keep ponderosa management in place and anticipated no changes in the company's operation
ponderosa, which was taken private in a $331 million buyout led by new york investor asher b. edelman in january 1987, is one of the nation's largest steakhouse chains, with annual sales of $500 million
the dayton, ohio-based company owns and operates 400 restaurants nationwide and franchises another 280 in the united states and canada, and has a meat processing and distribution operation through its esi meats inc. unit
after edelman acquired the company he sold off a number of assets, including most of its casa lupita restaurants and a meat-processing company, to help pay off debt used to finance the buyout
we believe that ponderosa is an outstanding company: it is strong and well-positioned with excellent management and great potential for growth and expansion,'' said stuart subotnick, metromedia executive vice president and general partner
metromedia formerly was the nation's biggest independent television and radio broadcasting company. john kluge, who owns 97 percent of the present company, liquidated most of its holdings after taking metromedia private in 1984
kluge has said he planned to use metromedia as the vehicle for a broad-based investment program. in addition to long-distance telephone operations, the company owns robotic painting and computer software companies
